#. Tag: title
#: security_ldap.xml:1207
#, no-c-format
msgid "Potential Security Risk with Caching"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_ldap.xml:1208
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using the cache incurs security risks, depending on the mechanism used."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: security_ldap.xml:1213
#, no-c-format
msgid "nscd"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_ldap.xml:1215
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you define an authorization rule (for example, members of group <literal>admin</literal> can log in), and you remove a user from that group, the client cache will not see that change until the cache expires or refreshes. So a user whose account has been revoked can still log in later."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: security_ldap.xml:1225
#, no-c-format
msgid "sssd"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_ldap.xml:1227
#, no-c-format
msgid "This caching mechanism constantly checks if group memberships are still valid. Thus the cache risk only exists if the <literal>sssd</literal> daemon is disconnected from the LDAP server for any reason."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: security_ldap.xml:1238
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specify the types of data that should be used from the LDAP source, such as <guimenu>Users</guimenu> and <guimenu>Groups</guimenu> , <guimenu>Super-User Commands</guimenu> , and <guimenu>Network Disk Locations</guimenu> (network-shared drives that can be automatically mounted on request)."
